<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1419&amp;p=14764#p14764</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1419&amp;p=14764#p14764"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: The new run/search box cannot be used to access UNC path]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1419&amp;p=14764#p14764"><![CDATA[
What if a new file is found while you press Enter? Then it will open that file instead of the path you typed. You have no way of knowing if new results will show up until the search is finished.<br />If your intent is to just open a folder, you can use the Win+R box, or even Win+E to open Explorer and type the path there.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2">Ivo</a> — Fri Sep 05, 2014 8:05 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
